Recipe.Name: Classic Beef Steak
Recipe.Description: A perfectly seared ribeye steak with herb butter, served with roasted vegetables.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Season steak with salt and pepper. 2. Heat cast iron pan until smoking. 3. Sear 4 min each side for medium-rare. 4. Rest 5 minutes. 5. Top with herb butter.

Recipe.Name: Truffle Risotto
Recipe.Description: Creamy Arborio rice infused with black truffle and aged Parmesan cheese.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Toast rice in butter. 2. Add white wine. 3. Gradually add warm broth, stirring constantly. 4. Finish with truffle oil and Parmesan.

Recipe.Name: Chocolate Lava Cake
Recipe.Description: Rich chocolate cake with a molten center, served with vanilla ice cream.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Melt chocolate and butter. 2. Whisk eggs and sugar. 3. Combine mixtures. 4. Add flour. 5. Bake at 425°F for 12 minutes.

Recipe.Name: Caesar Salad
Recipe.Description: Crisp romaine lettuce with homemade Caesar dressing and garlic croutons.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Make dressing with anchovy, garlic, egg yolk, lemon. 2. Toss romaine. 3. Add croutons and Parmesan. 4. Serve immediately.

Recipe.Name: Miso Glazed Salmon
Recipe.Description: Fresh Atlantic salmon with sweet white miso glaze and sesame seeds.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Mix miso, mirin, sake, sugar. 2. Marinate salmon 30 min. 3. Broil 8-10 minutes. 4. Garnish with sesame and scallions.

Recipe.Name: French Onion Soup
Recipe.Description: Caramelized onion soup topped with crusty bread and melted Gruyère cheese.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Slowly caramelize onions 45 min. 2. Add beef broth and wine. 3. Simmer 15 min. 4. Top with bread and cheese. 5. Broil until bubbly.

Recipe.Name: Tiramisu
Recipe.Description: Classic Italian dessert with espresso-soaked ladyfingers and mascarpone cream.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Whip mascarpone with sugar and egg yolks. 2. Dip ladyfingers in espresso. 3. Layer cream and cookies. 4. Refrigerate 4 hours. 5. Dust with cocoa.

Recipe.Name: Lobster Bisque
Recipe.Description: Velvety smooth lobster soup with a hint of brandy and fresh tarragon.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Sauté lobster shells with aromatics. 2. Add tomato paste. 3. Simmer with stock. 4. Strain and blend. 5. Finish with cream and brandy.

Recipe.Name: Pad Thai
Recipe.Description: Classic Thai stir-fried rice noodles with shrimp, egg, and tamarind sauce.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Soak rice noodles. 2. Make tamarind sauce. 3. Stir-fry shrimp and egg. 4. Add noodles and sauce. 5. Top with peanuts and lime.

Recipe.Name: Chicken Parmesan
Recipe.Description: Breaded chicken cutlet topped with marinara and melted mozzarella.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Bread chicken cutlets. 2. Pan-fry until golden. 3. Top with marinara and cheese. 4. Bake until cheese melts. 5. Garnish with basil.

Recipe.Name: Beef Tacos
Recipe.Description: Seasoned ground beef in corn tortillas with fresh salsa and guacamole.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Brown beef with spices. 2. Warm tortillas. 3. Make fresh salsa. 4. Prepare guacamole. 5. Assemble and serve.

Recipe.Name: Tom Yum Soup
Recipe.Description: Spicy and sour Thai soup with shrimp, mushrooms, and lemongrass.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Simmer broth with lemongrass and galangal. 2. Add mushrooms. 3. Add shrimp. 4. Season with fish sauce and lime. 5. Garnish with cilantro.

Recipe.Name: Crème Brûlée
Recipe.Description: Silky vanilla custard with a caramelized sugar crust.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Heat cream with vanilla. 2. Whisk egg yolks with sugar. 3. Combine and strain. 4. Bake in water bath. 5. Torch sugar topping.

Recipe.Name: Kung Pao Chicken
Recipe.Description: Spicy Sichuan stir-fry with chicken, peanuts, and dried chilies.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Marinate chicken. 2. Make Kung Pao sauce. 3. Stir-fry chicken. 4. Add vegetables and peanuts. 5. Toss with sauce.

Recipe.Name: Caprese Salad
Recipe.Description: Fresh mozzarella, ripe tomatoes, and basil with balsamic glaze.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Slice mozzarella and tomatoes. 2. Arrange alternating slices. 3. Add fresh basil. 4. Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic. 5. Season with salt.

Recipe.Name: Beef Bourguignon
Recipe.Description: Classic French beef stew braised in red wine with mushrooms and pearl onions.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Brown beef chunks. 2. Sauté vegetables. 3. Add wine and broth. 4. Braise 2-3 hours. 5. Add mushrooms and onions.

Recipe.Name: Sushi Roll
Recipe.Description: Fresh salmon and avocado rolled in seasoned rice and nori.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Prepare sushi rice. 2. Toast nori. 3. Spread rice on nori. 4. Add fillings and roll. 5. Slice and serve with soy sauce.

Recipe.Name: Guacamole
Recipe.Description: Fresh avocado dip with lime, cilantro, and diced tomatoes.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Mash ripe avocados. 2. Add lime juice. 3. Mix in onion and cilantro. 4. Add diced tomatoes. 5. Season with salt.

Recipe.Name: Mushroom Soup
Recipe.Description: Creamy wild mushroom soup with thyme and a touch of sherry.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Sauté mixed mushrooms. 2. Add shallots and garlic. 3. Pour in broth. 4. Blend until smooth. 5. Finish with cream and sherry.

Recipe.Name: Apple Pie
Recipe.Description: Classic American dessert with spiced apple filling in flaky crust.
Recipe.InstructionSet: 1. Make pie dough. 2. Slice and season apples. 3. Fill pie shell. 4. Add top crust. 5. Bake at 375°F for 50 minutes.
